<h2>JavaScript Hoisting</h2>

<p>With <b>let</b>, you cannot use a variable before it is declared:</p>

<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
// Check the console, this next line will produce an error:
carName = "Volvo";
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = carName;
let carName;
</script>

</body>
